data.directions: Just go straight from the front door and take a right when you get past the bar. There are two different bathrooms, both with unmarked doors.
data.comment: Open seven days a week. The food, a blend of Latin and South American, is absolutely incredible, and the posters don't lie when they advertise the best mojitos in New York - I recommend stopping in for a meal if you can! Casual-to-classy dress. The staff's pretty chill if you just need the restroom, though.

data.name: Adelphi Manhattan Center School of Social Work
data.directions: When you enter the campus, the bathrooms are the first left right next to the entrance doors. The gender-neutral bathroom is along the wall, so you'll need to turn around at the end of the hallway to see it.
data.comment: You'll need to show ID on the first floor to get a visitor's pass to enter the building, and you'll need to sign in at the Adelphi front desk. If you're an Adelphi student, you can use your student ID for both checkpoints. The Adelphi campus is a safe space, so no worries about harassment.

data.name: Bluestockings (bookstore)
data.directions: Bathroom is all the way in the back on the right, past the counter.
data.comment: Website: http://www.bluestockings.com. The people there are either queer or queer-knowledgeable and will probably understand if you need to use a safe bathroom (though it is mad small, approx. the size of a small closet); you don't have to buy things. If you have a few minutes and/or a few dollars to spend, though, take a peek through the shelves!

data.name: Cake Shop
data.directions: On the first floor there's a gender neutral single stall bathroom that's handicapped accessible. There are 2 other bathrooms downstairs that I didn't get a good look at but I believe are also single stall.
data.comment: They are very laid back and most of the shows there are free so I'd imagine as long as you're quick about it they wouldn't give you a hard time about using the upstairs restroom, or either of the downstairs ones as long as the doors are open. The upstairs one is just past the bar near the door to the basement.

data.comment: Open during the day, this bathroom is clean, spacious with soft lighting, art and potted plants!

data.name: Legal Action Center
data.comment: You have to be on the security list to get into the building. But if you have an appointment with any of the businesses in the building (at least on the fourth floor but probably other floors too) you'll be able to use a single stall bathroom.
